# KDE Plasma does not have an equivalent to Mutter's mutter-device-ignore property.
# Stripping ID_INPUT tags (the old approach) hides devices from ALL consumers
# including libinput, which breaks headless Sway input passthrough.
#
# Input isolation is handled by the Sway config:
# - "input * events disabled" disables all physical devices
# - Specific Sunshine passthrough devices are enabled individually
#
# KWin may see the virtual devices but cannot grab them since Sway runs in its own
# session with separate input handling. If you still experience input leaking to KDE,
# use seatd to run headless Sway on a separate seat (see AGENTS.md for details).
